When using the multi-cursor mode, when pasting from the clipboard the results are sometimes in reverse order.  The order of the data should be retained and not reversed.

Steps to reproduce (windows default key bindings)
1. alt+click on two or more places and hold shift (or ctrl+shift) and use the arrow keys to select some text.
2. ctrl+c to copy text
3. alt+click on the same number of lines as are copied on the clipboard where the pasted data should be placed
3. past data, notice that the results are in reverse order

``` javascript
var dataload;
var apiLogs;
var tenant;
```

Pasting the results in the data in the wrong order as follows:

``` javascript
var dataload = api;
var apiLogs = tenant;
var tenant = apiLogs;
var api = dataload;
```

I'm looking for clarification on the intended use of the api's in a "normal" extension vs a language server. It's common to give users the choice between an action happening when files are saved or as the user types. In a normal extension that uses the `vscode` api directly, the following is possible:

``` javascript
this.documentListener = vscode.workspace.onDidChangeTextDocument(this.handleChange);
this.documentListener = vscode.workspace.onDidSaveTextDocument(this.handleSave);
```

The object passed to the functions contains a nice `languageId` field to check to make sure you're only dealing with the right types of files.

The [official example](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode-languageserver-node-example) illustrates it being done a bit differently in language servers. File changes are synced using a nice `documentSelector` which automatically handles the `languageId` above. To handle file saves, though, a file system watcher is used which only accepts a glob pattern. This example shows the `createFileSystemWatcher` call being used for `.clientrc` files, but if the extension needs to monitor `cpp` files, each possible C++ extension would have to be included in the blob. Have I missed a part of the api or is this the intended way for a language server to be able to respond to saves?

Language Client:

``` javascript
let clientOptions: LanguageClientOptions = {
    documentSelector: ['plaintext'],
    synchronize: {
        configurationSection: 'languageServerExample',
        fileEvents: workspace.createFileSystemWatcher('**/.clientrc')
    }
}
```

Language Server:

``` javascript
documents.onDidChangeContent((change) => {
    validateTextDocument(change.document);
});

connection.onDidChangeWatchedFiles((change) => {
    connection.console.log('We recevied an file change event');
});
```
